This paper discusses a method for diagnosing software problems through combining logical and uncertain reasoning analyses. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the use of probabilistic reasoning methods indicates a potential fit with the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The focus on program understanding and debugging suggests a possible fit with the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. Finally, the integration of logical and uncertain reasoning methods may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
